com&ctz=America/Los_Angeles" style="border: 0" width="800" height="600" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>";s:10:"post_title";s:16:"Sailing Calendar";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:16:"sailing-calendar";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-12-03 21:45:20";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-12-03 21:45:20";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:3:"528";s:4:"guid";s:33:"http://198.1.99.216/?page_id=1072";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1046";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-11-20 17:09:29";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-20 17:09:29";s:12:"post_content";s:8850:"<a title="How do I get to LAMI?"><strong>How do I get to LAMI?</strong></a>
In San Pedro take Harbor Blvd to 6th Street.¬† Turn east on 6th.¬† It dead ends at the Maritime Museum.¬† You can only turn right onto Sampson Way.¬† Follow Sampson into Ports o‚Äô Call Village.

&nbsp;

<a title="To get to the vessels and/or the DECK House dockside facility"><strong>To get to the vessels and/or the DECK House dockside facility:</strong></a>
Turn left on Nagoya Way into Ports o‚Äô Call Village and go to Berth 78. The sign for it is yellow and black, but it‚Äôs a bit difficult to find.¬† Look instead for the San Pedro Fish Market.¬† Our dock is to the right of the Fish Market, and is visible across an open grass area.¬† Park near the grass area (it‚Äôs free!) and take the sidewalk at the right side of the grass near the Candy Shop.¬† The sidewalk dead ends, then turns right.¬† Just beyond the turn, you‚Äôll find the gate to our dock on your left. DECK House is the second shop (#P-3) on your right.

&nbsp;

<a title="To get to the office (Berth 73, Suite 2)"><strong>To get to the office (Berth 73, Suite 2):</strong></a>
Stay on Sampson Way past two stop signs ‚Äì Nagoya Way and Skytower Way.¬† At the third stop sign, you‚Äôll see an off-white, two-story building with a green stripe and signs for Utro‚Äôs restaurant.¬† Turn left at that stop sign and follow the road around till you can turn right into the small parking lot by the restaurant.¬† Our office is in the top story of the building.¬† The door is past the front of the restaurant.

&nbsp;

<a title="f I want to become a volunteer, how do I get started?"><strong>If I want to become a volunteer, how do I get started?</strong></a>
First, attend an orientation meeting.¬† They are held at our DECK House facility the third Saturday of each month (except December) at 10 AM.¬† See above for directions.

&nbsp;

<a title="I‚Äôm interested in your Youth Crew program"><strong>I‚Äôm interested in your Youth Crew program.¬† How do I get involved/get my child involved?</strong></a>
Youth Crew is for ages 13-19.¬† Click here or email <a href="mailto:youthcrew@lamitopsail.org">youthcrew@lamitopsail.org</a> for details.

&nbsp;

<a title="Where do I get finger printing done and how much does it cost?"><strong>Where do I get finger printing done and how much does it cost?</strong></a>
<a href="%20http://safesecureusa.com/" target="_blank">¬†http://safesecureusa.com/</a> We ask a $25.00 donation.¬† Please remit to LAMI.

&nbsp;

<a title="What should I bring when I come to sail?"><strong>What should I bring when I come to sail?</strong></a>
<p class="p1"><em>¬†For a day sail:</em></p>

<ul>
	<li class="p1">lunch</li>
	<li class="p1">refillable water bottle</li>
	<li class="p1">wear comfortable clothing</li>
	<li class="p1">dress in layers</li>
	<li class="p1">jacket (windbreaker)</li>
	<li class="p1">tennis or outdoor shoes</li>
	<li class="p1">sunglasses</li>
	<li class="p1">sunblock</li>
	<li class="p1">hat that won‚Äôt blow off</li>
</ul>
<p class="p1"><em>¬†For a voyage:</em></p>

<ul>
	<li class="p1">pack light, as there is very little storage space</li>
	<li class="p1">sleeping bag or blankets</li>
	<li class="p1">pillow</li>
	<li class="p1">sheet for mattress in bunk</li>
	<li class="p1">toiletries</li>
	<li class="p1">bathing suit</li>
	<li class="p1">towel</li>
</ul>

&nbsp;

<a title="What is appropriate attire when working with kids or the public"><strong>What is appropriate attire when working with kids or the public?</strong></a>

<ul>
	<li class="p1">Crew shirts are worn for all day sails, the first day of a voyage, and any time the vessel enters or leaves a port.</li>
	<li class="p1">Khaki, tan, or navy blue pants or shorts are preferred.¬† Jeans are ok, too.¬† Dirty, soiled, torn clothing is fine for maintenance days, but not for working with students.¬† Same goes for short shorts and tank tops or camisoles.</li>
	<li class="p1">Bathing suits are encouraged for voyages, but please be conscious of how revealing they are.</li>
</ul>

&nbsp;

<a title="How long do sails last"><strong>How long do sails last?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">Day sails generally run 3-5 hours.¬† Voyages vary from 3-5 days.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="What will my jobs on the boat will be my responsibility?"><strong>What will my jobs on the boat will be my responsibility?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">Everything!¬† Setting and taking in sail, furling (folding and putting away sail), tending docklines, doing deck washes, cooking, cleaning (we all contribute), navigating, helming, working in the rig, sanding painting, putting protective pine tar on stays...¬† Any job on the boat is available to you, but above all, your task is to be a good shipmate and make anyone who comes aboard feel welcome and included.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="I‚Äôm scared of heights."><strong>I‚Äôm scared of heights. Do I have to climb aloft?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">No.¬† Everything we do aloft in the rig is ‚Äúchallenge by choice.‚Äù¬† That option applies equally to volunteers and students.¬† (If you want to try, though, we‚Äôre always ready to encourage you and help you do so safely.)</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="What if I get seasick?"><strong>What if I get seasick?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">There are many methods to prevent seasickness.¬† Dramamine, Bonine, Meclazine, and other over the counter anti-seasickness medications are available at local drug stores.¬† There also are patches to wear behind your ears and pressure point wristbands that help.</p>
<p title="p1">And there‚Äôs no shame in seasickness.¬† It happens to all of us.¬† Don‚Äôt let it stop you from joining us.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="Is there a place for me with LAMI if I decide sailing isn‚Äôt for me"><strong>Is there a place for me with LAMI if I decide sailing isn‚Äôt for me or if kids aren‚Äôt my favorite thing in the world?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">Yes!¬† We have plenty of shore-based, student-free projects with which we always need help:</p>

<ul>
	<li class="p1">Maintenance</li>
	<li class="p1">Office help</li>
	<li class="p1">Grant writing</li>
	<li class="p1">Publicity</li>
	<li class="p1">Fundraising</li>
	<li class="p1">Boat tours</li>
	<li class="p1">Canvas/sail repair</li>
	<li class="p1">Carpentry</li>
	<li class="p1">Diesel / outboard engine repair and maintenance</li>
	<li class="p1">Electrical</li>
	<li class="p1">Plumbing</li>
	<li class="p1">Web design</li>
	<li class="p1">Food preparation</li>
	<li class="p1">Retail</li>
</ul>
<p class="p1">...and more!</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="I‚Äôve never sailed"><strong>I‚Äôve never sailed.¬†How much experience do I need?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">None!</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="How do I sign up to sail?"><strong>How do I sign up to sail?</strong></a>

<ul>
	<li class="p1">Check the <a href="/come-aboard/sailing-schedule/">Sailing Calendar</a> to find dates that work with your schedule</li>
	<li class="p1">Call the office at (310) 833-6055</li>
	<li class="p1">Ask for ‚ÄúBig Ben‚Äù and let him know with which school or event you‚Äôd like to participate</li>
	<li class="p1">Ben‚Äôs email:¬† <a href="mailto:bigben@lamitopsail.org" target="_blank">bigben@lamitopsail.org</a></li>
	<li class="p1">Please give at least 24 hours notice if you must cancel</li>
</ul>

&nbsp;

<a title="How do I get one of those cool crew shirts"><strong>How do I get one of those cool crew shirts I see everyone wearing?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">You earn your crew shirt when you‚Äôve contributed 40 hours of volunteer time to the organization.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="How often am I required to sail?"><strong>How often am I required to sail?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">There is no required amount of time.¬† You join us when you can, but you must complete two crew training sessions and be finger printed before you begin sailing with students.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="tall ship festivals"><strong>What are these ‚Äútall ship festivals‚Äù you talk about?</strong></a>
<p class="p1">Once a year, a group of tall ships get together in a few local ports ‚Äì LA, San Diego, and Dana Point are frequent stops.¬† We open to the public for tours and ‚Äúbattle sails‚Äù (re-enactments of tactics from the Age of Sail).¬† These gatherings are a chance to interact with other sailors and show the public a part of our world.¬† They‚Äôre a lot of work and a lot of fun.</p>

&nbsp;

<a title="What kinds of questions might I have to answer if I work at a festival"><strong>What kinds of questions might I have to answer if I work at a festival?</strong></a>
<p class="p1"><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Tall-Ship-FAQ-hand-out.pdf" target="_blank">Click here</a> for a frequently asked questions sheet.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:6:"F.A.Q.";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:3:"faq";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-11-26 05:42:34";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-26 05:42:34";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:33:"http://198.1.99.216/?page_id=1046";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"629";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-11-03 21:24:50";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-03 21:24:50";s:12:"post_content";s:1425:"<a title="TopSail Youth Program" href="/programs/topsail-youth-program/"><strong>TOPSAIL YOUTH PROGRAM</strong></a>

Los Angeles Maritime Institute‚Äôs award-winning TopSail Youth Program exposes youth to a world beyond their communities where they are provided with real-life challenges and hands-on learning not available in the traditional classroom. Youth who have participated in our program become role models for other youth, demonstrating firsthand the power of at-sea experiences to change lives! <a href="/programs/topsail-youth-program/">Learn more</a>.

&nbsp;

<a title="TopSail S.T.E.A.M. Program" href="/programs/topsail-s-t-e-a-m-program/"><strong>TOPSAIL S.T.E.A.M. PROGRAM</strong></a>

Our TopSail S.T.E.A.M. Program builds on our signature program and expands the S.T.E.A.M. framework inherent to our program. <a href="/programs/topsail-s-t-e-a-m-program/">Learn more</a>.

&nbsp;

<a title="Youth Crew Program" href="/programs/youth-crew-program/"><strong>YOUTH CREW PROGRAM</strong></a>

This volunteer program for ages 13-19 has become well established as a vital component of LAMI‚Äôs mission. <a href="/programs/youth-crew-program/">Learn more</a>.

&nbsp;

<a title="Why Sail Training" href="/programs/why-sail-training/"><strong>WHY SAIL TRAINING</strong></a>

A ship at sea has been described as a microcosm of the planet. <a href="/programs/why-sail-training/">Learn more</a>.";s:10:"post_title";s:8:"Programs";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:8:"programs";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-11-26 05:27:13";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-26 05:27:13";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:32:"http://198.1.99.216/?page_id=629";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:5;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"611";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2014-11-03 21:06:11";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2014-11-03 21:06:11";s:12:"post_content";s:3948:"Los Angeles Maritime Institute is an extraordinary place. The opportunities we provide for volunteers are nearly endless.

<em>Never sailed before?</em> No problem. We‚Äôll teach you.

<em>Have a ton of sailing experience?</em> Great! Come add to it and put your skills to the test in a very different environment.

<em>Enjoy working with kids?</em> Excellent. You‚Äôll thrive with us.

<em>Convinced kids are not your calling?</em> Give us a chance. We‚Äôll show you how satisfying putting others first can be.

<em>Think sailing might not be for you?</em> Our at-sea operations require a lot of dockside support, and we always need help with them. There is constant demand in the following areas:
<ul>
	<li>General boat maintenance ‚Äì sanding, oiling, painting, cleaning the vessels</li>
	<li>Canvas/sail repair</li>
	<li>Carpentry</li>
	<li>Marine Diesel maintenance</li>
	<li>Electrical systems maintenance</li>
	<li>Plumbing</li>
	<li>Fundraising</li>
	<li>Grant writing</li>
	<li>Office projects</li>
	<li>Web design</li>
	<li>Food preparation</li>
	<li>Retail/sales</li>
</ul>
‚Ä¶and much more! If you have the knowledge or desire to learn, we have a place for you.

The bottom line is ‚Äì the only thing necessary to succeed and have a truly rewarding experience with us is time and a willing attitude.

<a title=""><strong>Ready to Volunteer?</strong></a>

You'll need to attend an orientation first. ¬†Orientations are typically held on the third Saturday of each month at 10:00am. ¬†Please <a title="Calendar" href="http://www.lamitopsail.org/come-aboard/sailing-calendar/" target="_blank">check our calendar</a> to confirm and email our Volunteer Coordinator, Marann, to RSVP at <a title="RSVP for Volunteer Orientation" href="mailto:VolunteerCoordinator@lamitopsail.org" target="_blank">VolunteerCoordinator@lamitopsail.org</a>.

For directions, please visit our Frequently Asked Questions <a title="Directions" href="http://www.lamitopsail.org/faq/" target="_blank">page</a>.

You can fill out the necessary forms at the orientation or you can fill them out in advance and bring with you. ¬†The forms are available on our website,¬†<a title="Volunteer Forms" href="http://www.lamitopsail.org/volunteer/forms-training-materials/" target="_blank">click here to download</a>.

